                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11364: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 3, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>327. Your 580, November 30, 5 p.m. The Department desires to be informed of any
                    information available since the dispatch of your telegram under reference and of
                    your present estimate in regard to this matter.<note n="73" xml:id="d835fn73"
                        >The Secretary of State in telegram No. 4, December 3, 7 p.m., informed
                        President Roosevelt, then at sea: “We have heard nothing further on the
                        question of a declaration of war by Japan.” Then followed a brief summary of
                        German moves. (793.94/11432)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
